raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Hapi" %}
{% set version = "1.3.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/MAfarrag/Hapi/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c0365cfda816b61d399b40fc575a110c62d38b76a32e0ac4024e73c8dc3e1d37

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:

  host:
    - python >=3.9
    - pip >=22.2.2
  run:
    - pip >=22.2.2
    - numpy >=1.21.2,<1.23.3
    - gdal >=3.3.3,<3.5.1
    - pyramids >=0.2.0
    - pandas >=1.3.2,<1.5.0
    - Rtree >=0.9.4
    - geopandas >=0.10.2
    - matplotlib >=3.4.2,<3.6.0
    - scipy >=1.9.1
    - statsmodels >=0.13.0
    - rasterstats >=0.16.0
    - oasis >=1.0.2
    - statista >=0.1.3
    - loguru >=0.5.3
    
test:
  imports:
    - Hapi

about:
  home: https://github.com/MAfarrag/HAPI
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.md
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.md
  summary: Distributed Hydrological model
  description: |
    This module builds Distributed Hydrological model.
  dev_url: https://github.com/MAfarrag/HAPI
  doc_url: https://hapi-hm.readthedocs.io/
  doc_source_url: https://github.com/MAfarrag/HAPI/master/README.md

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - MAfarrag
